    diaTribe College Day 2018

    August 1, San Francisco, CA

    RSVP
    About the Event

    Want a personal look into some amazing colleges? Come to our college panel! Alumni and current students from a wide range of colleges will answer questions about applications, academics, student life, financials, athletics, and more. These individuals have navigated the complicated path of college and landed jobs, internships, and research experiences in areas they're passionate about. If that sounds like what you want to do and you want advice on how to achieve your goals, don't miss our college panel on August 1st!

     

     

    Are you worried about college? Does the application process seem more stressful than it needs to be? Are you worried about what it will be like when you get there? Talk to people who actually know and want to help you on this path.

     

    The diaTribe Foundation is hosting a series of lightning panels of students and alums from across the nation … and they want to talk to you!

     

    You can expect to walk away with your questions answered, and a better picture of what life in college actually looks like. From academics to extracurriculars and social life, we’ll cover it all! Join us for some delicious refreshments and an eye-opening info session Wednesday, August 1st at 1-3pm. We can’t wait to see you there!​

    Walk away with knowledge on

    ​

    • Academics

    • Research, internships, job hunt, building resume, pre-professional track, prepare for careers in medicine, digital health, life sciences, research and development, and technology

    • Social life

    • Potential opportunities in athletics

    • How to reduce stress and do exceptionally well

    Speakers

    ...and more!
